│ \"cannot split on     │
│ multi incoming        │
│ phis\");\n```\nThis   │
│ assertion checks that │
│ the block being split │
│ does not contain a    │
│ PHI node with         │
│ multiple incoming     │
│ edges. However, it    │
│ does not account for  │
│ degenerate cases      │
│ where the block has a │
│ single instruction or │
│ terminator. In such   │
│ cases, the            │
│ transformation may    │
│ produce an invalid    │
│ CFG (Control Flow     │
│ Graph).\n\n### 4.     │
│ Proposed Edit         │
│ Points(s)\nTo fix the │
│ issue, we should      │
│ modify the assertion  │
│ to include an         │
│ additional check for  │
│ degenerate blocks.    │
│ Specifically, we      │
│ should ensure that    │
│ the block being split │
│ has more than one     │
│ instruction:\n```cpp\ │
│ nassert((!isa<PHINode │
│ >(*I) ||              │
│ getSinglePredecessor( │
│ )) &&\n               │
│ \"cannot split on     │
│ multi incoming        │
│ phis\");\nassert(size │
│ () > 1 && \"cannot    │
│ split degenerate      │
│ blocks\");\n```\nThis │
│ change ensures that   │
│ the transformation    │
│ only proceeds for     │
│ valid blocks,         │
│ preventing the        │
│ creation of invalid   │
│ CFGs.\n\n### 5.       │
│ Conclusion\nThe       │
│ proposed fix adds a   │
│ safeguard against     │
│ splitting degenerate  │
│ blocks, addressing    │
│ the root cause of the │
│ issue. This change is │
│ expected to prevent   │
│ the creation of       │
│ invalid IR and        │
